{#
	reCAPTCHA v3 — invisible, score-based. Only exposes the (public) site
	key here; Components/contactForm.ts loads Google's script itself, and
	only after cookie consent is granted (it sets Google cookies, so it's
	gated like any other non-essential tracker — see Components/
	cookieConsent.ts). Verified server-side in modules/contactform/
	Module.php, which treats a missing token as "consent declined or JS
	disabled," not spam — the honeypot alone covers that case.
#}
{% set recaptchaSiteKey = recaptchaSiteKey() %}

{% if recaptchaSiteKey %}
<script>
	window.recaptchaSiteKey = {{ recaptchaSiteKey|json_encode|raw }};
</script>
{% endif %}
